This paper deals with speech emotion recognition using both audio and text features, which falls under the sub-category of multimodal learning (cs.MM). The paper also uses traditional machine learning classifiers and deep learning models, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of statistical learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to extract features from the text domain, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of ambiguity resolution in communication, which is related to the sub-category of speech and natural language processing (cs.SD).
